    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>NEWARK MONORAIL</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By RONALD SMOTHERS</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Smothers, Ronald</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Port Authority of NY and NJ plans to add 57 buses and vans this weekend to take up slack as repairs begin on monorail at Newark International Airport (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Starting this weekend, the Port Authority of New York and New Jersey will add 57 buses and vans to the 62,000 vehicles on the roads at Newark International Airport each day. The shuttles will take up the slack as repairs begin on the airport monorail, which has carried 30,000 people a day. Initially only the ends of the 1.9-mile system will be closed, but after Labor Day the entire system will be closed for three months.</p>
        <p>RONALD SMOTHERS</p>
      </block>
